-> To create a new project
nest new project_name
-> To generate a module
nest g module module_name
-> To generate a service
nest g service service_name --no-spec
-> Nest js also has some npm packages, one of them is config
npm i @nestjs/config

-> Prisma
npx prisma init
npx prisma migrate dev

-> To run a specific service from docker-compose file
docker-compose up dev-db -d

-> To create a hook that will run before a script in package.package.json
-> this script will run before test:e2e script in package.json
-> I'm not using Docker that's why I'm not using it
- "pretest:e2e": "npm run db:test:restart"

